data.text:
At Rider:

Communication major.

At: Wilson High School:

Four-year letterwinner in basketball, volleyball and track and field…Berks County Female Athlete of the Year according to the Reading Eagle...All-Division honoree all four years for basketball, scoring over 1,000 career points with the team winning the district title twice and the County championship two times…for volleyball, recorded over 1,000 kills and holds the Wilson school record for aces and kills in a season…four-time All-District honoree for volleyball…threw the shot put and discus in track, earning All-County honors in both three times…team won two County championships…holds the Wilson discus (137’5”) and shot put records (40’10”)…earned a fifth place finish at the 2014 Penn Relays in the discus…sixth in both the shot put and discus at the PIAA championship meet...Wilson High School Pepsi Female Athlete of the Year as a senior…academic honor roll all four years of high school…personal: daughter of Mark and Alison Wallace…older brother Ben and younger sister Jennifer…her mother (Alison) is in the Albright College Basketball Hall of Fame with over 1,000 points and over 1,000 rebounds and her father (Mark) played Division II football at Edinboro University.
